Here Guy l’Estrange the sheriff has been allowed >830 85. 4d. for the pay of twenty serjeants at Oswestry for a year at rd. a day. At the end of his account are the words ‘Idem vicecomes debet 745. de Retracta liberationis Servientum de Blancmuster.' That is to say he had kept back so much of the sum allowed and was therefore accountable for it at the Exehequer. The sum was paid into the Treasury in the 18th year.
